signature: static <E> E get(final Iterator<E> iterator, final int index)

enhanced_by.reason: Setting up the iterator with a collection is often necessary before accessing elements by index.
Validating the index to ensure it is within bounds is a common precondition for accessing elements by index.
Both methods retrieve an element by index, making them functionally similar for assertion construction.
Both methods involve index-based operations and can handle similar exceptions, such as IndexOutOfBoundsException.
